 in \n    the message with the letter that appears 2 places ahead of that \n    vowel in the english alphabet. \n    Assume only letters. \n    \n    Examples:\n    >>> encode(\'test\')\n    \'TGST\'\n    >>> encode(\'This is a message\')\n    \'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG\'\n    """\n \n        IMPORTANT REQUIREMENTS:  \n        1. Save the code to a file named \'encode.py\'  \n        2. The file must be saved in the project directory: "/Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline"  \n        3. The file should contain ONLY the function implementation with proper imports  \n        4. Ensure the file is written to disk before completing the task  \n        \n        '}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '[Message] from Mike to David: David, please execute the following to fulfill the user’s requirement.\n\nTask: Write encode.py with the Python function encode(message) and validate.\nProject directory: /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline\nTarget file: /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/encode.py\nLanguage: Python 3.10+\n\nExact file content to write:\n\ndef encode(message: str) -> str:\n    """\n    Write a function that takes a message, and encodes in such a \n    way that it swaps case of all letters, replaces all vowels in \n    the message with the letter that appears 2 places ahead of that \n    vowel in the english alphabet. \n    Assume only letters. \n    \n    Examples:\n    >>> encode(\'test\')\n    \'TGST\'\n    >>> encode(\'This is a message\')\n    \'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG\'\n    """\n    swapped = message.swapcase()\n    out = []\n    for ch in swapped:\n        if ch in \'aeiouAEIOU\':\n            out.append(chr(ord(ch) + 2))\n        else:\n            out.append(ch)\n    return \'\'.join(out)\n\nSteps:\n1) mkdir -p /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline\n2) Write the file at /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/encode.py with ONLY the function above (no tests, no prints, no main).\n3) Validate:\n   cd /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline && python3 - << \'PY\'\nfrom encode import encode\nassert encode(\'test\') == \'TGST\'\nassert encode(\'This is a message\') == \'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG\'\nprint(\'OK\')\nPY\nAcceptance criteria:\n- File exists and contains only the function implementation.\n- Validation prints OK.\n- Reply when complete.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '\n# Past Experience\n<experience>\n\n# Tool State\n\n\n# Current Plan\n[GOAL] [Message] from Mike to David: David, please execute the following to fulfill the user’s requirement.\n\nTask: Write encode.py with the Python function encode(message) and validate.\nProject directory: /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline\nTarget file: /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/encode.py\nLanguage: Python 3.10+\n\nExact file content to write:\n\ndef encode(message: str) -> str:\n    """\n    Write a function that takes a message, and encodes in such a \n    way that it swaps case of all letters, replaces all vowels in \n    the message with the letter that appears 2 places ahead of that \n    vowel in the english alphabet. \n    Assume only letters. \n    \n    Examples:\n    >>> encode(\'test\')\n    \'TGST\'\n    >>> encode(\'This is a message\')\n    \'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG\'\n    """\n    swapped = message.swapcase()\n    out = []\n    for ch in swapped:\n        if ch in \'aeiouAEIOU\':\n            out.append(chr(ord(ch) + 2))\n        else:\n            out.append(ch)\n    return \'\'.join(out)\n\nSteps:\n1) mkdir -p /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline\n2) Write the file at /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/encode.py with ONLY the function above (no tests, no prints, no main).\n3) Validate:\n   cd /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline && python3 - << \'PY\'\nfrom encode import encode\nassert encode(\'test\') == \'TGST\'\nassert encode(\'This is a message\') == \'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG\'\nprint(\'OK\')\nPY\nAcceptance criteria